==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ending
<hw>End"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Termination; concluding part; result; conclusion; destruction;
death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The final syllable or letter of a
word; the part joined to the stem. See 3d <er>Case</er>, 5.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ending day</b></col>, <cd>day of death.</cd>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endite</ent>⟦br⟧
